{
  "title": "Procedure → procedure_occurrence",
  "notes": "Branch: the Procedure edge (`mapspec/etl/Procedure__procedure_occurrence.sql`, stage-1 view `mapspec/views/Procedure__procedure_occurrence.view.json`). The varying input dimension across these variants is the **code vocabulary / domain routing / status / timezone** of a single Procedure; the Patient (`patient-1`, female, born 1960-05-12) and Encounter (`enc-1`) are held constant so the diffs are crisp.\n\nHow the edge works (read off the SQL):\n1. Stage-1 fans the `code.coding[]` out into four nullable columns by `system`: `code_snomed` (`http://snomed.info/sct`), `code_cpt4` (`http://www.ama-assn.org/go/cpt`), `code_hcpcs` (`https://www.cms.gov/Medicare/Coding/HCPCSReleaseCodeSets`), `code_icd10pcs` (`http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/icd-10-pcs`).\n2. Stage-2 re-UNIONs those into `(staging_id, prio, vocab, code)` rows with priority SNOMED=1 → CPT4=2 → HCPCS=3 → ICD10PCS=4, joins `vocab.concept (src) → concept_relationship 'Maps to' (invalid_reason IS NULL) → vocab.concept (std, standard_concept='S', domain_id='Procedure')`, then `DISTINCT ON (staging_id) ORDER BY prio` keeps the single highest-priority coding **that resolves to a Procedure-domain standard concept**.\n3. `procedure_concept_id` = std concept; `procedure_source_concept_id` = src concept; `procedure_source_value` = the raw code string of the winning coding.\n4. `procedure_type_concept_id` is the hardcoded constant 32827 ('EHR encounter record', Type Concept, standard).\n5. Dates: `COALESCE(performedDateTime, performedPeriod.start)` drives `procedure_date`/`procedure_datetime`; `performedPeriod.end` drives `procedure_end_*`. Every instant is cast `::timestamptz AT TIME ZONE 'UTC'` (procedures.csv stores UTC `Z`; FHIR may carry a local offset) — so a non-UTC offset shifts the wall-clock and can roll the calendar date.\n6. `provider_id` = hash of `performer.first().actor` reference; `visit_occurrence_id` = hash of `encounter`; `person_id` = hash of `subject`.\n7. Row filter: `WHERE COALESCE(status,'completed') NOT IN ('entered-in-error','not-done','unknown')`.\n8. `modifier_concept_id`, `quantity`, `visit_detail_id`, `modifier_source_value` are never populated by this edge (no bodySite read) → always NULL.\n\nGrounding (verified live in vocab.concept on the v20260227 bundle): SNOMED 430193006 → concept 4326177 'Medication reconciliation' (standard, Procedure; 'Maps to' is the self-loop 4326177→4326177, so std==src). HCPCS A4736 → concept 2614995 'Topical anesthetic, for dialysis, per gram' (standard, Procedure; self-map). SNOMED 73211009 → concept 201820 'Diabetes mellitus' (standard, **Condition** — used for the domain-filter negative case). Type concept 32827 'EHR encounter record' (Type Concept, standard). NOTE: **CPT4 is not loaded in this Athena bundle** (the licensed CPT4 names require the UMLS post-processing step `cpt.sh`, which was not run — `vocab.concept` has 0 CPT4 rows). So in variant (b) the CPT4 coding cannot resolve at all in-bundle; SNOMED still wins because its prio=1 short-circuits the DISTINCT ON regardless. Variant (b') re-proves the same priority mechanism with HCPCS as the loser, where the loser *would* resolve to a distinct Procedure concept (2614995) but is dropped by prio ordering — that is the strongly-grounded priority assertion.\n\nFK refs are symbolic: `ref:patient-1` = referenceToId(Patient/patient-1), `ref:enc-1` = referenceToId(Encounter/enc-1), `ref:prac-1` = referenceToId(Practitioner/prac-1). `omop: {}` means the pipeline emits ZERO rows for that variant.",
